tournament.motion: This house would not allow Siripala to destroy the art Siripala, a private art collector, owns a valuable piece of art that is of extreme importance to Sri Lanka's heritage. In his will, he has instructed that the painting be cremated with him.

This house, as the US government, would end federal subsidies for Mysore's research Shreesh Mysore is a researcher at Johns Hopkins University conducting federally-subsidised live animal experiments on barn owls and their neurological structures. While previous research into links between mammal and bird brains have created significant advances in science, Mysore's experiments include openly operating on the brains of unsedated owls. Animal rights groups such as PETA have begun litigation to stop the experiments.

This house supports preventative detention Preventative detention would allow for high-risk individuals to be detained before they may commit a crime. This detention could include but is not limited to measures such as house arrest or mandated psychiatric care.
This house, as the LGBT movement, would abandon the narrative that queer children should be loved because parental love should be unconditional.
This house believes that feminists should advocate for the destruction of the traditional family unit
This house would ban religious practices where individuals harm themselves (eg. self-impalement by Hindus, Christian sects whipping themselves etc.)
On balance, this house believes that trade unions have done more harm than good in Sri Lanka.

This house prefers a world in which the majority of people believe in moral pessimism rather than moral optimism. Moral pessimism is the belief that humans are innately bad, and need to learn morality from external sources, fighting their inner urges to be better. Moral optimism is the belief that humans are innately good, and need to follow their true self and overcome societal expectations to be better.
This house believes that professional sports teams should not be permitted to draft players without secondary education

TH, As Siripala would accept Elon Musk's Job offer

Siripala is a middle-aged Sri Lankan man living with his wife and a teenage child. He has been diagnosed with diabetes and, in addition, lost an arm in a brutal accident. This unfortunate event reduced his ability to work, leading to a significant decline in his family's income. The family now faces serious financial challenges. Despite his circumstances, Siripala has two potential opportunities ahead of him.

One option is a traditional job that would not be impacted by his disability, allowing him to continue contributing to his family’s income and maintaining his current way of life.

The other opportunity is a new offer from Elon Musk to be a Neuralink test subject, which will provide greater levels of monetary compensation but also comes with potential future health risks due to the unproven technology. Additionally, it would require him to be flown to the US, thereby sacrificing a sense of normalcy.

Siripala will also be provided with a bionic arm and a job at one of Elon Musk's companies, contributing to society.

THBT States should not allow its citizens to holiday in countries with a poor human rights record

THP a monarchy where the king has the divine right to rule, as opposed to a theocracy ruled by religious institutions

The Divine Right of Kings is a political and religious doctrine of a monarchy. It follows that only God can judge a monarch, and that any attempt to depose, dethrone, resist, or restrict their powers runs contrary to God's will and may constitute a sinful act.

In a theocracy, without the concept of the Divine Right of Kings, religious leaders and institutions govern the state directly and have divine authority on Earth.

THBT the majority of Sri Lankan citizens will not get into secular heaven

Secular heaven is an afterlife in which people are permanently fulfilled and happy.

This heaven is guarded by an omnipotent being who assesses your actions, their consequences, and the intentions behind those actions. If you are judged net positively, you will be admitted.
